Juventus reached the Champions League semi-finals after beating Monaco 0-0 on Wednesday . 
  The Italian champions lost to AC Milan in the 2003 final at Old Trafford . 
  Gianluigi Buffon scored the winning penalty in the shoot-out . 
  Juventus have endured a difficult period since the 2003 defeat . 
  They were relegated to Serie B but are now in the elite of Europe . 
  Bayern Munich, Real Madrid and Barcelona await in the last four . 
  Andriy Shevchenko scored the winner for Juventus in that final . 
 